Abstract

Is climate change real? Nobody cares. We look at how climate change and health are taking the center stage in UN General Debates.

Basic description of the data.

#Loading packages and data
library(readtext)
library(quanteda)

if (!require("readtext")) devtools::install_github("kbenoit/readtext")
DATA_DIR <- "~/Dropbox/Research/UN Data/" 
ungd_files <- readtext(paste0(DATA_DIR, "Converted sessions/*"), 
                                 docvarsfrom = "filenames", 
                                 dvsep="_", 
                                 docvarnames = c("Country", "Session", "Year"))
#changing row.names to have only country_year, rather than folder pathway from `readtext`.
row.names(ungd_files) <- str_replace(str_replace(sapply(str_split(row.names(ungd_files), "/"),`[`,2), ".txt", ""), "_\\d{2}", "")
if (!require("quanteda")) devtools::install_github("kbenoit/quanteda")
ungd_corpus <- corpus(ungd_files, text_field = "text") 
#Creating corpus for 2014, for Wordscore example below
ungdc.2007 <- corpus_subset(ungd_corpus, Year==2007)
ungdc.lancet <- corpus_subset(ungd_corpus, Year>2006)

Tokenizing corpus.

#Tokenization and basic pre-processing
tok <- tokens(ungdc.lancet, what = "word",
              remove_punct = TRUE,
              remove_symbols = TRUE,
              remove_numbers = TRUE,
              remove_twitter = TRUE,
              remove_url = TRUE,
              remove_hyphens = TRUE,
              verbose = TRUE)
Starting tokenization...
...tokenizing 1 of 1 blocks
, removing URLs...serializing tokens 32602 unique types
...total elapsed:  2.313 seconds.
Finished tokenizing and cleaning 1,928 texts.

Removing any digits and punctuation, that may be part of tokens (through mistakes in OCR). Also, removing any tokens less than three characters.

#Removing any digits and punctuation, that may be part of tokens (through mistakes in OCR).
#Removing any tokens less than three characters.
tok.m <- tokens_select(tok, c("[\\d-]", "[[:punct:]]", "^.{1,2}$"), 
                       selection = "remove", 
                    valuetype="regex", verbose = TRUE)
tok.r <- tokens_tolower(tok.m)

Creating dictionary

mylist <- list( c("malaria"), c("diarrhoea"), c("infection"), c("disease"), c("sars"), c("measles"), c("pneumonia"), c("epidemic"), c("pandemic"), c("public", "health") , c("health","care"), c("epidemiology"), c("healthcare"), c("health"), c("mortality"), c("morbidity"), c("nutrition"), c("illness"), c("infectious"), c("ncd"), c("non-communicable", "disease"), c("noncommunicable","disease"), c("communicable", "disease"), c("air", "pollution"), c("nutrition"), c("malnutrition"), c("mental", "disorder"), c("stunting"), c("climate","change"), c("global","warming"), c("green","house"), c("temperature"), c("extreme","weather"), c("global", "environmental", "change"), c("climate","variability"), c("greenhouse"), c("low","carbon"), c("ghge"), c("renewable","energy"), c("carbon","emission"), c("co2","emission"), c("climate","pollutant")) 
 
tok.compound <- tokens_compound(tok.r, mylist, valuetype = "fixed", concatenator = "_")
mydict <- dictionary(list(health = c("malaria", "diarrhoea", "infection", "disease", "sars", "measles", "pneumonia", "epidemic", "pandemic", "public_health", "health_care", "epidemiology", "healthcare", "health", "mortality", "morbidity", "nutrition", "illness", "infectious", "ncd", "non-communicable_disease", "noncommunicable_disease", "communicable_disease", "air_pollution", "nutrition", "malnutrition", "mental_disorder", "stunting"), 
                          climate =  c("climate_change", "global_warming", "green_house", "temperature", "extreme_weather", "global_environmental_change", "climate_variability", "greenhouse", "low_carbon", "ghge", "renewable_energy", "carbon_emission", "co2_emission", "climate_pollutant")))

KWIC

This is for Health related terms.

tok.hea <- kwic(tok.compound, c("malaria", "diarrhoea", "infection", "disease", "sars", "measles", "pneumonia", "epidemic", "pandemic", "public_health", "health_care", "epidemiology", "healthcare", "health", "mortality", "morbidity", "nutrition", "illness", "infectious", "ncd", "non-communicable_disease", "noncommunicable_disease", "communicable_disease", "air_pollution", "nutrition", "malnutrition", "mental_disorder", "stunting"), window = 50, valuetype = "regex")

Climate change related terms.

tok.cc <- kwic(tok.compound, c("climate_change", "global_warming", "green_house", "temperature", "extreme_weather", "global_environmental_change", "climate_variability", "greenhouse", "low_carbon", "ghge", "renewable_energy", "carbon_emission", "co2_emission", "climate_pollutant"), window = 50, valuetype = "regex")

Here were getting the intersection of health and climate. We take tokens associated with health terms (50 tokens before and after each health related key term) and within this set of tokens we perform KWIC for climate change selected terms. We limit the window here to 10 in order to get at this intersection.

tok.x <- kwic(as.tokens(tok.hea), c("climate_change", "global_warming", "green_house", "temperature", "extreme_weather", "global_environmental_change", "climate_variability", "greenhouse", "low_carbon", "ghge", "renewable_energy", "carbon_emission", "co2_emission", "climate_pollutant"), window = 10, valuetype = "regex")

Using UN M49 Standard (Standard country or area codes for statistical use (M49)) we create regional and sub-regional groupings of countries. [https://unstats.un.org/unsd/methodology/m49/]

regions <- read.csv("UNSD - Methodology.csv")
regions$ISO.alpha3.Code <- as.character(regions$ISO.alpha3.Code)
regions$Region.Name <- as.character(regions$Region.Name)
regions$Sub.region.Name <- as.character(regions$Sub.region.Name)
temp$V1 <- str_replace(temp$V1, "YUG", "SRB")
regional_data <- inner_join(temp, regions, by = c("V1" = "ISO.alpha3.Code"))
reg_dataframe <- as.data.frame(table(regional_data$Region.Name, regional_data$V2))
reg_sum <- summarise(group_by(reg_dataframe, Var1, Var2), count = sum(Freq))
reg_sum$Var2 <- as.numeric(as.character(reg_sum$Var2))
ggplot(reg_sum, aes(x=Var2, y=count, group=Var1, colour = Var1, linetype = Var1)) +
  geom_line() +
  guides(colour=guide_legend(title=NULL), linetype = FALSE) +
  theme_bw() +
  ggtitle("Political engagement with the intersection of climate change and health") + 
  ylab("Total number of references per UNGD session") + xlab("Year") 
  ggsave("intersection_by_region.pdf")
